Southampton midfielder, James Ward-Prowse, has revealed what manager Ralph Hasenhuttl told the team, during the half time of their 1-1 draw with Manchster United on Saturday. The Saints went in a goal down at the break, after Daniel James broke the deadlock with a superb effort. However, Jannik Vestergaard headed in the equalizer for the hosts around the half hour mark, to snatch one point. Ward-Prowse speaking to BT Sport, said: “(The message at half-time was) ‘not to panic’. “We were quite comfortable during the game and we kept believing in what we were doing. “We had to be patient and the giant at the back popped up with a great header.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.